SIMPLE: robbery
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Robbery
<hw>Rob"ber*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Robberies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[OF.
<ets>roberie</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or practice of
robbing; theft.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thieves for their <qex>robbery</qex> have authority⟦br⟧
When judges steal themselves.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The crime of robbing. See
<er>Rob</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>, 2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Robbery</xex>, in a strict sense, differs from
<xex>theft</xex>, as it is effected by force or intimidation, whereas
<xex>theft</xex> is committed by stealth, or privately.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Theft; depredation; spoliation; despoliation;
despoilment; plunder; pillage; rapine; larceny; freebooting;
piracy.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Robbin</ent>⟦br⟧
